com.googlecode.objectify.cmd

Interface QueryKeys<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Key<T>>, QueryExecute<Key<T>>, com.google.appengine.api.datastore.QueryResultIterable<Key<T>>

    public interface QueryKeys<T>
extends QueryExecute<Key<T>>

    After you call Query.keys(), you are executing a keys-only query. This is the command structure. It offers only terminators; if you wanted additional filtering, add it before keys().

    There is one additional method beyond the standard QueryExecute interface: the asEntities() method lets you return your keys as partial entities.

    Author:
    Jeff Schnitzer

      QueryExecute<T> asEntities()
      Instead of getting keys, return the key data as partial entites - POJO objects whose key (id/parent) fields have been set but are otherwise uninitialized.

    • Method Detail

      • first

        Ref<T> first()
        Gets the first entity in the result set. Obeys the offset value.
        Returns:
        the first instance in the result, asynchronously. The Ref will contain null if the result set was empty. Because this is a keys-only fetch, the Ref value will hold a partial entity.

      • asEntities

        QueryExecute<T> asEntities()
        Instead of getting keys, return the key data as partial entites - POJO objects whose key (id/parent) fields have been set but are otherwise uninitialized.
